article.description: Justyna Podziemska scored 19 points and Aubrey Vandiver added 17 to help lead Wyoming (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) to a 68-46 victory against Colorado State on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Podziemska leads Wyoming past Colorado State
article.linkText: Cowgirls open with 25-8 run, cruise by Rams
article.story:
LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- Justyna Podziemska scored 19 points and Aubrey Vandiver added 17 to help lead No. 24 Wyoming to a 68-46 victory against Colorado State on Wednesday night.

Hanna Zavecz finished with 14 points and four assists for Wyoming (23-4, 11-3 Mountain West).

The Cowgirls hit three unanswered 3-pointers to cap a 25-8 run to start the game. They led 32-14 at halftime and went ahead 48-18 with 15 minutes remaining. Colorado State (2-24, 0-13) trailed by 20 points or more throughout the final 19 minutes of the game.

Juanise Cornell led the Rams with 12 points, and Amaka Uzomah had eight points and 11 rebounds.
